New Records: Chris Woakes has gone level with Ian Botham on 30 wickets, the joint-most for England at World Cups.
Key Match Events: England won by 160 runs to boost Champions Trophy qualification chances.
Rashid & Moeen took three wickets each, Willey struck twice, Woakes claimed one and Barresi was run out.
Malan made 87 off 74, Woakes hit 51 off 45.
Chris Woakes and David Willey struck in the powerplay to put England thoroughly in control of the game.
Ben Stokes and Chris Woakes built a 129-run stand.
England ended a run of five successive defeats to pick up their second win of the World Cup.
Post-Match Reflections: Netherlands captain Scott Edwards: 'We didn't start well, our bowlers did well to drag it back but they took it away from us and got just above par. Same old story with the bat.'

England captain Jos Buttler: 'We were desperate for the win. We got off to a great start, had a bit of a speed bump in the middle. We needed someone to stand up and take charge. There was some very smart cricket between Stokes and Woakes to get us to that score.'
Player of the match, England's Ben Stokes: 'I'm more pleased for us to get a victory over the line, it's been a tough World Cup and nice to get back to winning ways today.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: England play Pakistan on Saturday. A win would almost certainly guarantee their place at the Champions Trophy but it doesn't necessarily.
England have climbed to seventh, and as things stand would qualify for the Champions Trophy in Pakistan in 2025.
